<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">General distribution: Southern Europe</emphasis>
: Albania, Bosnia, Bulgaria, Croatia, France, Greece, Italy, North Macedonia, Portugal, Romania, Slovenia, Serbia, Spain; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Central Europe</emphasis>
: Austria, Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, Slovakia; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Eastern Europe</emphasis>
: Moldova, Russia (South European Russia), Ukraine; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Middle East</emphasis>
: Iran, Israel, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Transcaucasia</emphasis>
: Azerbaijan, Georgia, Russia (Chechnya); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Central Asia</emphasis>
: Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Northern Africa</emphasis>
: Morocco, Tunisia (summarised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J P" journalOrPublisher="Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742783" refString="Duffels, J P, van der Laan, P A, 1985. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956-1980. Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980" year="1985">Duffels and van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, Allen F" journalOrPublisher="Academic Press / Elsevier, London, UK" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743532" refString="Sanborn, Allen F, 2014. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea. Academic Press/Elsevier, London, UK" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea" year="2014">Sanborn 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
There is a doubious citation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" genus="Oligoglena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oligoglena tibialis" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Oligoglena tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Germany (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaltenbach, A" journalOrPublisher="Naturgeschichte Wiens" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="447 - 494" refId="B6075852" refString="Kaltenbach, A, Steiner, H, Aschenbrenner, L, 1972. Die Tierwelt der Trockenlandschaft. Naturgeschichte Wiens 2: 447 - 494" title="Die Tierwelt der Trockenlandschaft" volume="2" year="1972">Kaltenbach et al. 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743322" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1972. Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" title="Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list" year="1972">Nast 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lodos, Niyazi" journalOrPublisher="Tuerkiye Bitki Koruma Dergisi" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="67 - 82" refId="B5743208" refString="Lodos, Niyazi, Kalkandelen, Ayla, 1981. Preliminary list of Auchenorrhyncha with notes on distribution and importance of species in Turkey. V. Families Flalidae, Ricaniidae and Cicadidae. Tuerkiye Bitki Koruma Dergisi 5 (2): 67 - 82" title="Preliminary list of Auchenorrhyncha with notes on distribution and importance of species in Turkey. V. Families Flalidae, Ricaniidae and Cicadidae" volume="5" year="1981">Lodos and Kalkandelen 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="536 - 661" refId="B5743312" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1987. The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Europe. Annales Zoologici 40 (15): 536 - 661" title="The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Europe" volume="40" year="1987">Nast 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau, Jose Alberto" journalOrPublisher="Rapport WWF, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="367 - 375" refId="B5743489" refString="Quartau, Jose Alberto, Fonseca, P J, 1988. An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea). In: Proceedings of the 6th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7-11 September 1987.: 367 - 375" title="An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea)" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 6 th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7 - 11 September 1987." year="1988">Quartau and Fonseca 1988</bibRefCitation>
), as it is not listed in the latest overview of fauna (
<bibRefCitation author="Nickel, H" journalOrPublisher="Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands, Band 4: Wirbellose Tiere (Teil 2)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B6075803" refString="Nickel, H, Achtziger, R, Biedermann, R, Bueckle, C, Deutschmann, U, Niedringhaus, R, Remane, R, Walter, S, Witsack, W, 2016. . Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands, Band 4: Wirbellose Tiere (Teil 2) 70 (4)" volume="70 (4)" year="2016">Nickel et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). There are also doubtful citations for Sicily (
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743322" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1972. Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" title="Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list" year="1972">Nast 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau, Jose Alberto" journalOrPublisher="Rapport WWF, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="367 - 375" refId="B5743489" refString="Quartau, Jose Alberto, Fonseca, P J, 1988. An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea). In: Proceedings of the 6th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7-11 September 1987.: 367 - 375" title="An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea)" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 6 th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7 - 11 September 1987." year="1988">Quartau and Fonseca 1988</bibRefCitation>
) and Crete (
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743322" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1972. Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" title="Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list" year="1972">Nast 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau, Jose Alberto" journalOrPublisher="Rapport WWF, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="367 - 375" refId="B5743489" refString="Quartau, Jose Alberto, Fonseca, P J, 1988. An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea). In: Proceedings of the 6th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7-11 September 1987.: 367 - 375" title="An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea)" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 6 th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7 - 11 September 1987." year="1988">Quartau and Fonseca 1988</bibRefCitation>
), as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" genus="Oligoglena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oligoglena tibialis" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Oligoglena tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been found in recent field research with bioacoustic methods on these Islands (Thomas Hertach, personal communication, 
<bibRefCitation author="Trilar, Tomi" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Slovenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="5 - 18" refId="B5743784" refString="Trilar, Tomi, Gogala, Matija, 2010. Tettigetta carayoni Boulard (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) from Crete, faunistic data and first description of its song. Acta Entomologica Slovenica 18 (1): 5 - 18" title="Tettigetta carayoni Boulard (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) from Crete, faunistic data and first description of its song" volume="18" year="2010">Trilar and Gogala 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Trilar, Tomi" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Slovenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="17 - 30" refId="B5743764" refString="Trilar, Tomi, Gogala, Matija, 2012. Pagiphora aschei Kartal (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) from Crete (Greece) - Distribution and description of its song. Acta Entomologica Slovenica 20 (1): 17 - 30" title="Pagiphora aschei Kartal (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) from Crete (Greece) - Distribution and description of its song" volume="20" year="2012">Trilar and Gogala 2012a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Distribution in Bulgaria</emphasis>
: This small cicada is the most abundant and most widespread species of singing cicadas found in Bulgaria. The data for 125 localities are known (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="F5781451" captionText="Figure 56. Map with localities of Oligoglena tibialis in Bulgaria. Black - literature data, blue - data from collections, red - bioacoustic data collected in this survey." figureDoi=".figure56" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407064" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">56</figureCitation>
). In literature, we found the data in 
<bibRefCitation author="Nedyalkov, N" journalOrPublisher="Periodichno spisanie na blgarskoto knizhovno druzhestvo (Periodical Journal of the Bulgarian Literary Society)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="670 - 692" refId="B5743331" refString="Nedyalkov, N, 1908. Treti prinos km entomologichnata fauna na Blgariya [Third contribution to the entomological fauna of Bulgaria]. Periodichno spisanie na blgarskoto knizhovno druzhestvo (Periodical Journal of the Bulgarian Literary Society) 69 (9-10): 670 - 692" title="Treti prinos km entomologichnata fauna na Blgariya [Third contribution to the entomological fauna of Bulgaria]" volume="69" year="1908">Nedyalkov (1908)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoakimov, D" journalOrPublisher="Sbornik za narodni umotvoreniya, nauka i knizhnina [Collection of folklore, science and literature]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="1 - 34" refId="B5743855" refString="Yoakimov, D, 1909. Po faunata na Hemiptera v Blgariya [On the fauna of Hemiptera of Bulgaria]. Sbornik za narodni umotvoreniya, nauka i knizhnina [Collection of folklore, science and literature] 25 (7): 1 - 34" title="Po faunata na Hemiptera v Blgariya [On the fauna of Hemiptera of Bulgaria]" volume="25" year="1909">Yoakimov (1909)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, Jiri" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="121 - 128" refId="B5742759" refString="Dlabola, Jiri, 1955. Faunistika a nektere nove druhy palearktickych krisu. [Faunistik und neue Arten der palaearktischen Zikaden (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha)]. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 30: 121 - 128" title="Faunistika a nektere nove druhy palearktickych krisu. [Faunistik und neue Arten der palaearktischen Zikaden (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha)]" volume="30" year="1955">Dlabola (1955)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bairyamova, Viola Kirilova" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="27 - 33" refId="B5742566" refString="Bairyamova, Viola Kirilova, 1976. Tsikadi (Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha) po dbovite gori v Strandzha [Cicadas (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) of oak forests of Strandzha Mt.]. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 5: 27 - 33" title="Tsikadi (Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha) po dbovite gori v Strandzha [Cicadas (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) of oak forests of Strandzha Mt.]" volume="5" year="1976">Bairyamova (1976)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelov, Venelin" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut de Zoologie et Musee" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="157 - 171" refId="B5743361" refString="Pelov, Venelin, 1968. Prinos km prouchvaneto na blgarskata tsikadna fauna (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha) [Beitrag zur Erforschung der bulgarischen zikadenfauna (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha)]. Bulletin de l'Institut de Zoologie et Musee 26: 157 - 171" title="Prinos km prouchvaneto na blgarskata tsikadna fauna (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha) [Beitrag zur Erforschung der bulgarischen zikadenfauna (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha)]" volume="26" year="1968">Pelov (1968)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bairyamova, Viola Kirilova" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="55 - 56" refId="B5742576" refString="Bairyamova, Viola Kirilova, 1992. Prouchvaniya vrkhu tsikadnata fauna (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) na Rodopite [Studies on cicade fauna (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) of the Rhodopes]. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 44: 55 - 56" title="Prouchvaniya vrkhu tsikadnata fauna (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) na Rodopite [Studies on cicade fauna (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) of the Rhodopes]" volume="44" year="1992">Bairyamova (1992)</bibRefCitation>
lists the species for Rhodope Mts. for xerophylous and mesophylous oak-horn forests 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">(Quercus-Carpinus)</emphasis>
between 700 and 1000 m and beech forests 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">(Fagus)</emphasis>
between 1000 and 1400 m and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bairamova, Viola Kirilova" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="15 - 21" refId="B5742556" refString="Bairamova, Viola Kirilova, 1978. Dendrofilni vidove tsikadi (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) po dbovite gori v Blgariya [Dendrophilous cicada species (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) found in oak forests in Bulgaria]. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 9: 15 - 21" title="Dendrofilni vidove tsikadi (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) po dbovite gori v Blgariya [Dendrophilous cicada species (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) found in oak forests in Bulgaria]" volume="9" year="1978">Bairamova (1978)</bibRefCitation>
mentions the species for oak forests 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">(Quercus)</emphasis>
. The species is also listed in overviews by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743322" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1972. Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" title="Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list" year="1972">Nast (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="536 - 661" refId="B5743312" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1987. The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Europe. Annales Zoologici 40 (15): 536 - 661" title="The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Europe" volume="40" year="1987">Nast (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lodos, Niyazi" journalOrPublisher="Tuerkiye Bitki Koruma Dergisi" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="67 - 82" refId="B5743208" refString="Lodos, Niyazi, Kalkandelen, Ayla, 1981. Preliminary list of Auchenorrhyncha with notes on distribution and importance of species in Turkey. V. Families Flalidae, Ricaniidae and Cicadidae. Tuerkiye Bitki Koruma Dergisi 5 (2): 67 - 82" title="Preliminary list of Auchenorrhyncha with notes on distribution and importance of species in Turkey. V. Families Flalidae, Ricaniidae and Cicadidae" volume="5" year="1981">Lodos and Kalkandelen (1981)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau, Jose Alberto" journalOrPublisher="Rapport WWF, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="367 - 375" refId="B5743489" refString="Quartau, Jose Alberto, Fonseca, P J, 1988. An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea). In: Proceedings of the 6th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7-11 September 1987.: 367 - 375" title="An annotated check-list of the species of cicadas known to occur in Portugal (Homoptera: Cicadoidea)" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 6 th Auchenorrhyncha Meeting, Turin, Italy 7 - 11 September 1987." year="1988">Quartau and Fonseca (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, but without exact location data for Bulgaria.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
In Bulgaria, it is distributed all over the country with known data in western Danubian Plane, eastern Danubian Plane, northern lowest hills of the Pre-Balkan, southern Lower Mountain Pre-Balkan, northern Balkan Mts., western Sub-Balkan valleys, Kraishte-Ichtiman, Vitosha Mt., True Sredna Gora Mt., Ograzhden-Vlachina Mts., Kyustendil-Blagoevgrad Middle Struma valley, Sandanski-Petrich Middle Struma valley, Pirin Mt., Dabrash-Batak western Rhodope Mts., Prespa-Chernatitsa western Rhodope Mts., Upper Thracian Plain, Tundzha-Burgas Valley, eastern Rhodope Mts., Haskovo Hills Land, Sakar Mt. and Strandzha Mt. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="F5781451" captionText="Figure 56. Map with localities of Oligoglena tibialis in Bulgaria. Black - literature data, blue - data from collections, red - bioacoustic data collected in this survey." figureDoi=".figure56" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407064" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
In this study, the majority of the population of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" genus="Oligoglena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oligoglena tibialis" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Oligoglena tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found between sea level and 800 m (91% of the population) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 57" captionStartId="F5781455" captionText="Figure 57. Altitudinal distribution of Oligoglena tibialis. The percentage of the recorded localities is displayed in 200 - metre altitude zones." figureDoi=".figure57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443808" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">57</figureCitation>
), but the rest is distributed between 801 and 1400 m. The highest find is registered at 1570 m a.s.l., where an unknown collector in Pamporovo collected one male and one female specimen, which are kept in the SOFM collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Acoustic behaviour</emphasis>
: The song was described by 
